Duties
If selected for this position, you will join a well-respected team that is responsible for the United States Attorney's Office of Western District of Missouri. You will be responsible for providing technical and advisory assistance to support the information management needs of the District. At the full performance level, typical work assignments will include:
Diagnosing and resolving problems in response to customer reported incidents;
Installing, configuring, troubleshooting, and maintaining customer hardware and software;
Providing for customer training including orientation for new users;
Maintaining network architecture and infrastructure, to include configuring and maintaining servers, hubs, routers, and switches;

Responsibilities will increase and assignments will become more complex as your training and experience progress.
